<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="12Aug1921"><font color="red">ca. 12 August 1921</font>, <cite>Letters I</cite> (JJ to Valery Larbaud): Mlle Monnier spoke to me of your impatience to read the last episode. But there are two, <cite>Ithaca</cite> and <cite>Penelope</cite>. Of the latter I have since the beginning sketched the outline and now I have filled in at least three quarters. Of the former I have written almost as much but it needs much more work. I work six hours a day in adding also text to the proofs which I correct &hellip; I  have added to <cite>Circe</cite> a Messianic scene with a litany sung in honour [of the titles of the adventures]  <p class="set">Kidney of Bloom, pray for us! <br>Flower of the Bath, pray for us! <br>Mentor of Menton, pray for us! <br>Canvasser of the Freeman, pray for us! <br>Charitable Mason, pray for us! <br>Wandering Soap, pray for us! <br>Music without Words, pray for us! <br>Reprover of the Citizen, pray for us! <br>Friend of all Frillies, pray for us! <br>Midwife Most Merciful, pray for us!</p> <p> [&hellip;] the last word of <cite>Ulysses</cite>. Here it is: yes.</p> </div>
